CNCP v1 24396
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12088: Incorrect vite warning regarding nesting tr directly in table element",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:09.376240+00:00",
  "text": "Incorrect vite warning regarding nesting tr directly in table element\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.5.10\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#eNp9kDELwjAQhf9KuVnqoJMUQcVBBxV1zFLrWatpEpKLFqT/3SSlrYN0CS/vexfe5QMLpeKXRZhBQlgqnhLOmYiihNILb6S/6Hkydkcg4xY51Y/ACMhkUtyKPH4YKdyLHx9nkMlSFRz1XlEhhWEwiwLxLOVcvrfBI21x1PrZHbPnH/9hKu8xOGg0qF/IoGOU6hypwevTDiunO1jKq+UuPQCPaCS3vmMTW1pxdbV/cqHtplRSUyHys1lXhMK0S/miPlmHPAP3rauB1fu6k3ga5pioof4CfnKCSA==\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate a SFC with this content.\r\n\r\n```\r\n<template>\r\n  <table>\r\n    <tr></tr>\r\n  </table>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\nVite will issue a warning:\r\n\r\n> warning: \\<tr> cannot be child of \\<table>, according to HTML specifications. This can cause hydration errors or potentially disrupt future functionality.\r\n\r\nThis warning is factually incorrect.  The [relevant spec](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-table-element) says that a `<table>` may contain:\r\n\r\n> In this order: optionally a [caption](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-caption-element) element, followed by zero or more [colgroup](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-colgroup-element) elements, followed optionally by a [thead](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-thead-element) element, followed by either zero or more [tbody](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-tbody-element) elements or one or more [tr](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-tr-element) elements, followed optionally by a [tfoot](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#the-tfoot-element) element, optionally intermixed with one or more [script-supporting elements](https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#script-supporting-elements-2).\r\n\r\nThis is because [htmlNesting.ts](https://github.com/vuejs/core/blob/29de6f8b0bb1a604f247b0712daac29e93aa6f3e/packages/compiler-dom/src/htmlNesting.ts#L63) does not list `tr` as a valid child of `table`, despite the spec allowing it.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nI expect no warning to be produced.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nA warning is produced from vite:\r\n\r\n> warning: \\<tr> cannot be child of \\<table>, according to HTML specifications. This can cause hydration errors or potentially disrupt future functionality.\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n+-- @vitejs/plugin-vue-jsx@3.1.0\r\n+-- @vitejs/plugin-vue@5.0.4\r\n+-- @vue/tsconfig@0.4.0\r\n+-- vite@5.4.8\r\n+-- vue-tsc@2.1.6\r\n`-- vue@3.5.10\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
